comments.body:
Gosh. Thanks for bisecting! I just found an issue in the commit, this would be the fix:

```
diff --git a/tcp_splice.c b/tcp_splice.c
index 473562b..483e45d 100644
--- a/tcp_splice.c
+++ b/tcp_splice.c
@@ -577,7 +577,7 @@ eintr:
                        if (conn->read[fromsidei] == conn->written[fromsidei])
                                break;

-                       conn_event(c, conn, OUT_WAIT(fromsidei));
+                       conn_event(c, conn, OUT_WAIT(!fromsidei));
                        break;
                }

```

> I can confirm this seems to fix the issue.

Thanks, I'll start preparing a new release right away, and try to reproduce it meanwhile, but the issue is quite obvious. From that commit:

```
@@ -644,8 +647,7 @@ eintr:
                        if (conn->read[fromsidei] == conn->written[fromsidei])
                                break;

-                       conn_event(c, conn,
-                                  fromsidei == 0 ? OUT_WAIT_1 : OUT_WAIT_0);
+                       conn_event(c, conn, OUT_WAIT(fromsidei));
                        break;
                }

```

but no, if the "from" side is 0, and we're waiting for the output ("to") side to be ready for writing, we need to wait on side 1, not 0. :(
